HEADWORD: Presentient
<hw>Pre*sen"tient</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>praesentiens</ets>, p. pr. of <ets>praesentire</ets> to perceive
beforehand; <ets>prae</ets> before + <ets>sentire</ets> to feel.]</ety>
<def>Feeling or perceiving beforehand.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Presentific</ent>⟦br⟧
